title: Johnsonville, LLC Recalls Smoked Pork Sausage Products due to Possible Foreign Matter Contamination
summary: WASHINGTON, March 15, 2018 Johnsonville, LLC, a Sheboygan Falls, Wis. establishment, is recalling approximately 109,603 pounds of smoked pork sausage products that may be contaminated with extraneous materials, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today.
